{"article_id":"QrEl0kXFaIYJFTXm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republican leaders faced an immediate backlash Thursday","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"after revealing their Obamacare replacement bill ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"leaving campaign vows","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to repeal the 2010 health care law","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"in doubt","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"as the Senate pushes toward a showdown on the chamber floor next week .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The bill ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"announced by Majority Leader Mitch McConnell ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"softens the edges of an earlier House version","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that President Trump reportedly called \" mean . \"","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"The 142-page plan would extend the life of President Obama ' s Medicaid expansion","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"and offer more generous subsidies for the poor and those","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"approaching retirement age .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"It removes Obamacare ' s \" individual mandate \"","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"and unwinds the health care exchanges ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"but it maintains the 2010 law ' s guarantees","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that let young adults stay on their parents ' plans","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"and guarantees coverage","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"despite pre-existing conditions .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"\" Obamacare is a direct attack on the middle class ,","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"and American families deserve better than its failing status quo","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"they deserve better care , \"","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Mr. McConnell said","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"as he went to the Senate floor","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"to publicly announce the plan ,","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"which was drafted in secret .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Democrats uniformly oppose the bill ,","depth":4},{"id":28,"text":"meaning Republicans can not lose more than two of their 52 members in a vote .","depth":4},{"id":29,"text":"Yet four have already said","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"they can ' t vote for it ,","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"as it stands .","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":3},{"id":33,"text":"Cassidy :","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"Republican health care bill should pass","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"once concerns are addressed","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"Sens . Rand Paul of Kentucky , Ron Johnson of Wisconsin , Ted Cruz of Texas and Mike Lee of Utah said","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"they opposed the draft legislation for a variety of reasons ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"but they are open to negotiation","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"before the bill hits the floor .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Mr. Johnson said","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"he feels rushed ,","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"while the others worry","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"that they are turning the dials on Obamacare","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"instead of fulfilling their pledge","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"to kill it .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"\" Somebody ' s going to have to look at this bill","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"and say","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"we ' re going to make it look more like repeal","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"and less like we ' re keeping Obamacare , \"","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Mr. Paul said .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"Democrats , meanwhile , say","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"the bill is still too much of a repeal and not enough of Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"They have said","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"they won ' t cooperate","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"until Republicans agree to keep the basic structure of the 2010 Affordable Care Act ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"then work on fixes .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"\" We live in the wealthiest country on earth .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"We ' re proud of it","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"as we should be .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"But surely , we can do better than what the Republican health care bill promises , \"","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"said Senate Minority Leader Charles E. Schumer , New York Democrat .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Democrats also have complained about the path of the bill ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"which Mr. McConnell wrote","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and which will head straight to the floor ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"bypassing the extensive committee process","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"that characterized the Obamacare debate .","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"Mr. McConnell promised to wait for a Congressional Budget Office evaluation of the bill","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"and said","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"there will be a robust floor debate ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"including amendments .","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"\" It ' s much better than Obamacare .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"I like this a lot better than the House bill , \"","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"said Sen. David Perdue , Georgia Republican .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Others said","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"they needed time","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"to read the whole bill ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"though they felt","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"the proposals were trending in the right direction .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"From the White House , President Trump said","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"the Senate ' s health care bill is in good shape","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"but needs a \" little negotiation . \"","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"The CBO is expected to release its score next week ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"detailing how the bill affects federal spending and health care coverage .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Its evaluation of the House bill ,","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"which passed that chamber last month ,","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"projected lower costs for most Americans","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"but said","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"the poor and those","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"approaching retirement age","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"would see premium hikes .","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"Some 23 million fewer Americans would hold insurance a decade from now","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"because Medicaid ' s rolls would be cut","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"and people would no longer be required by law to purchase insurance .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Senators tried to lower costs for the poor and older Americans ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"pegging tax credits for people","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"who buy insurance on their own","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"to their amount of income instead of just age .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"That cuts a middle ground between the House plan and Obamacare .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"\" For example , the tax credits for older folks","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"- people like me -","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"are now age-adjusted and income-adjusted ,","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"so someone","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"who is making $ 20,000 a year and 62 years old","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"would be able to afford coverage under this ,","depth":15},{"id":105,"text":"where under the","depth":15},{"id":106,"text":"[ House bill ]","depth":17},{"id":107,"text":"I think","depth":17},{"id":108,"text":"it was problematic","depth":17},{"id":109,"text":"if they could afford coverage , \"","depth":17},{"id":110,"text":"said Sen. Bill Cassidy , a Louisiana Republican and physician .","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"The plan also goes more slowly","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"in curtailing Obamacare ' s expansion of Medicaid ,","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"which the House plan froze in 2020 .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"The Senate bill would begin a gradual reduction in 2021","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"and return to pre-Obamacare levels in 2024 .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"To placate fiscal hawks ,","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"the plan would allow Medicaid spending to rise at a slower rate than under the House version ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"starting in 2025 .","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"Republicans say","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"reining in Medicaid spending will force states to focus on those","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"who need it most ,","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"though moderates worry","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that the cuts will suddenly pull coverage from needy residents","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"and cripple the fight against opioid addiction .","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"The federal-state program covers 1 in 5 Americans , about half of U.S. births and two-thirds of nursing home residents .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"A number of Republicans withheld judgment ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"they will go back and talk to their governors and state health care officials","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"and see how the bill affects them .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"\" At first glance , I have serious concerns about the bill ' s impact on the Nevadans","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"who depend on Medicaid , \"","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"said Sen. Dean Heller , Nevada Republican and a key holdout .","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"He is considered one of the most vulnerable Republicans on an otherwise favorable Senate electoral map next year .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"Another swing vote , Sen. Susan M. Collins of Maine , said","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"the plan has pros and cons","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"that deserve more scrutiny .","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"The bill would let states use Obamacare ' s waiver system","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"to drop aspects of the 2010 law ,","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"including its list of essential benefits","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"that plans must cover .","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"However , states can not let insurers deny people with pre-existing conditions or charge them more than healthy consumers , a concept","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"known as \" community rating . \"","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"Mr. Cruz and Mr. Lee had been pushing to scrap more of the regulations on insurers , not less ,","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"and House conservatives","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"who will revisit the final plan","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"insisted on letting states waive community rating .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"The bill does strip federal funding from Planned Parenthood , the country ' s largest network of abortion clinics ,","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"making good on a Republican campaign pledge .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"In a boon for insurers , Republicans said","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"the bill would maintain through 2019 the cost-sharing payments to insurance companies","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"that cover out-of-pocket health care expenses of the poor .","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"Mr. Trump has threatened to withhold those payments .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"The plan would repeal Obamacare ' s taxes on health insurers , medical device makers and high earners , among others ,","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"prompting Democrats to blast it as a wealth transfer from the needy to those","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"who are doing fine .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"\" Let ' s be very clear :","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"Senate Republicans are paying for tax cuts for the wealthy with American lives , \"","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"said Sen. Elizabeth Warren , Massachusetts Democrat .","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"Mr. Obama also weighed in","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"to decry the changes to his signature law .","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"\" The Senate bill ,","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"unveiled today ,","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"is not a health care bill .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"It ' s a massive transfer of wealth from middle-class and poor families to the richest people in America , \"","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"Mr. Obama said on Facebook .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"\" It hands enormous tax cuts to the rich and to the drug and insurance industries ,","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"paid for","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"by cutting health care for everybody else . \"","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"Republicans have described their repeal effort as a mission","depth":7},{"id":170,"text":"to rescue Americans from a law","depth":8},{"id":171,"text":"headed for failure .","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"They point to rising premiums and dwindling choices ,","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"as insurers pull out of markets .","depth":7},{"id":174,"text":"Sen. John Cornyn , Texas Republicans , said","depth":7},{"id":175,"text":"the cruelest lawmakers of all were Democrats","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"defending the \" failed experiment \" of Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":177,"text":"\" They may not be willing to help ,","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"but we will , \"","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"\" And we will get it done","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"and help the American people","depth":9},{"id":182,"text":"who are being hurt by the failure of Obamacare today . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":365,"left":214,"right":364,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":209,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":188,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":0,"right":187,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":186,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":1,"right":185,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":184,"right":4,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":184,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":200,"right":207,"relation":"e